CALL FOR PAPERS : New Deadline - 10th May 2005

=20

4=E8mes JOURNEES INTERNATIONALES DE LA LINGUISTIQUE DE CORPUS

=20

4th International Corpus Linguistics Meeting in Lorient 15 - 17 =
septembre 2005

=20

http://www.univ-ubs.fr/crellic/

=20

The 4th "Journ=E9es de la linguistique de corpus" corpus linguistics =
meeting will be held in Lorient on the 15th, 16th and 17th September =
2005. They are organised by the ADICORE research group of the University =
of South Brittany, Lorient, France.

=20

The call is open to all researchers working on corpora, whatever the =
language of study. The languages of the conference is French and =
English, there will be no translation facilities.

=20

Invited Speakers

=20

We are pleased to announce that plenary papers will be presented by =
Professor Wolfgang Teubert, University of Birmingham, and Professor Jean =
V=E9ronis, University of Aix-en-Provence.

=20

Objectives

The 4th "Journ=E9es de Linguistique de Corpus", like their predecessors =
aim to promote the development of corpus linguistics in France. They =
bring together researchers from a wide variety of backgrounds, the =
central issue being the use of computational tools in the study of =
corpora. Proposals would normally fall under one of the following =
headings:

  a.. mono~ and bilingual lexicology and lexicography,
  b.. quantitive linguistics,
  c.. terminology and terminography
  d.. translation studies
  e.. discourse analysis,
  f.. applied and descriptive linguistics
  g.. ... .
=20

Languages

French and English

=20

Organisation

Full papers of 20 minutes in length plus question time on current work =
in the field. There will also be a possibility for poster presentations. =
Selected papers and posters will be published in the conference =
proceedings

=20

Proposals

A long proposal of the contribution (two pages is required). This =
proposal should contain at least one paragraph presenting the corpus =
used for the study and the means of analysis for which the main findings =
to be presented at the conference.  The proposal should be accompanied =
by a separate page containing information on the authors, namely name, =
university or research group, telephone and fax details, postal and =
electronic address. The proposal should be in Times 12, or equivalent, =
with single interline, in a Word RTF, or HTML format.  =20

=20

Proposals will be evaluated in a blind review procedure by two members =
of the review panel. They should be sent to the following address:

=20

Geoffrey Williams

D=E9partement LEA,

U.F.R. Lettres et Sciences Humaines

4 rue Jean Zay,=20

